title: Grants volunteer ambulance workers preferential treatment when applying to medical schools within New York state which receive funding from the state
summary: Grants volunteer ambulance workers preferential treatment when applying to medical schools within New York state which receive funding from the state where there are applicants of otherwise equal qualifications.
actClause: AN ACT to amend the volunteer ambulance workers' benefit law, in relation to granting the emergency medical technicians preference to medical school admissions to all schools which receive funding from New York state
